{"type":"message","id":"961b9cd1","parentId":"e41366be","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:25:12.996Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 17:25 GMT+2] OPERATION: GREEN BADGE RESCUE.\n\n1.  **Badge Repair (`README.md`):**\n    *   *Audit:* Check URL structure for Shields.io.\n    *   *Fix:* Use `https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/ci-cd.yml?branch=dev` for Build Status.\n    *   *License:* Ensure path is `github/license/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot`.\n\n2.  **CI/CD Pipeline Fix (`.github/workflows/ci-cd.yml`):**\n    *   *Problem:* Python 3.14-dev is often missing in standard runners or flaky.\n    *   *Solution:* Fallback to `3.13`. Use `3.14.0-alpha.0` explicitly if needed, but 3.13 is safer for \"Green Light\".\n    *   *Mocking:* Ensure `env` variables `DRY_RUN=true` are set in the workflow YAML to prevent network calls.\n\n3.  **Local Verification:**\n    *   Run `pytest` one last time.\n\n4.  **Git Operations:**\n    *   `git add .github/workflows/ci-cd.yml README.md`\n    *   `git commit -m \"fix: repair broken README badges and stabilize CI/CD for Python 3.14\"`\n    *   `git push origin dev`\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   List of badge URLs fixed.\n    *   CI/CD config diff (Python version).\n    *   Commit Hash."}],"timestamp":1771169112994}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a4505ab","parentId":"961b9cd1","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:25:17.750Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Understanding the Task Scope**\n\nI'm currently reviewing `README.md` and `.github/workflows/ci-cd.yml`. My primary goal is to grasp the specifics of the badge implementation within the README and to assess the stability of the CI/CD pipeline defined in the YAML file. I need to fully understand both before I start any changes.\n\n\n**Assessing Initial Findings**\n\nI've finished reading the initial files. I've noted the location of the build status badge in `README.md`. Now, I'm working to understand the Shields.io URL format for the `dev` branch. Next, I'll need to figure out what adjustments, if any, the CI/CD pipeline needs.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771169117630_407","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"README.md"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771169117745_408","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":".github/workflows/ci-cd.yml"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4835,"output":141,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4976,"cost":{"input":0.00967,"output":0.0016920000000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011362}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771169112996}}
{"type":"message","id":"dc1cc2af","parentId":"8a4505ab","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:25:17.775Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771169117630_407","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 🤖 DMarket Telegram Bot (High-Frequency Trading Edition)\n\n[![CI](https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/actions/workflows/ci-cd.yml/badge.svg?branch=dev)](https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/actions/workflows/ci-cd.yml)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot)](LICENSE)\n![Latency](https://img.shields.io/badge/Latency-30ms-brightgreen?logo=speedtest)\n![Skills](https://img.shields.io/badge/Skills-CS2%20%7C%20Dota2%20%7C%20Rust%20%7C%20TF2-orange)\n![Arch](https://img.shields.io/badge/Arch-Event--Driven-blueviolet)\n![Activity](https://img.shields.io/github/commit-activity/m/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot)\n![Style](https://img.shields.io/badge/Code%20Style-Black-000000)\n\n> **Enterprise-grade automation** for DMarket interaction, featuring sub-millisecond latency and robust multiprocessing architecture powered by Gemini AI.\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ Performance Dashboard\n\n| Metric | Standard Bot | MyClawDev (HFT) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Response Time** | `500ms` | **`0.03ms`** |\n| **Throughput** | `10 req/s` | **`1000+ req/s`** |\n| **Uptime** | `99.0%` | **`99.99%`** |\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 AI Stack\n\nWe leverage a dual-model approach for optimal performance:\n\n*   **Gemini Pro 1.5**: Handles complex reasoning, market trend analysis, and strategic decision-making.\n*   **Gemini Flash**: Dedicated to ultra-low latency execution for arbitrage opportunities and sniping.\n\n---\n\n## 🏗️ Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    Master[Master Controller] --> Redis[(Redis Message Broker)]\n    Redis --> CS2[CS2 Worker]\n    Redis --> Dota[Dota2 Worker]\n    Redis --> Rust[Rust Worker]\n    Redis --> TF2[TF2 Worker]\n    \n    style Master fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style Redis fill:#ff9,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style CS2 fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n    style Dota fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n    style Rust fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n    style TF2 fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n```\n\n---\n\n## 📜 Version History\n\n*   **v2.1:** Docker, GHCR, Enterprise CI/CD.\n*   **v2.0:** Multiprocessing, 40 Skills, 0.03ms Latency.\n*   **v1.0:** SACS-2026, Ed25519, Hot Reload.\n*   **v0.1:** Legacy script (Broken Async).\n\n## 🎮 Commands\n\n### General\n*   👋 `/start` - Initialize the bot interaction.\n*   ❓ `/help` - Show available commands.\n*   📊 `/status` - Check system health and uptime.\n*   ⚙️ `/settings` - Configure bot preferences.\n\n### Trading\n*   💰 `/balance` - View current DMarket balance.\n*   📦 `/inventory` - List items in inventory.\n*   📉 `/price <item>` - Check price for a specific item.\n*   🛒 `/buy <item>` - Initiate a buy order.\n*   🏷️ `/sell <item>` - Initiate a sell order.\n\n### Automation\n*   🤖 `/auto_buy` - Toggle auto-buy module.\n*   🔄 `/auto_sell` - Toggle auto-sell module.\n*   📜 `/history` - View transaction history.\n*   🛑 `/stop` - Emergency stop all active tasks.\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Deployment\n\n### Docker (Recommended)\n\n```bash\ndocker pull ghcr.io/dykij/dmarket-telegram-bot:latest\ndocker run -d --env-file .env ghcr.io/dykij/dmarket-telegram-bot:latest\n```\n\n### Manual\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot.git\ncd DMarket-Telegram-Bot\npip install -r requirements.txt\npython main.py\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771169117774}}
{"type":"message","id":"8989ce75","parentId":"dc1cc2af","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:25:17.782Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771169117745_408","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"name: CI/CD Pipeline\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [ \"main\", \"dev\" ]\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [ \"main\", \"dev\" ]\n\njobs:\n  linting:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up Python\n        uses: actions/setup-python@v4\n        with:\n          python-version: \"3.11\"\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: |\n          python -m pip install --upgrade pip\n          pip install flake8\n          if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi\n      - name: Lint with flake8\n        run: |\n          # stop the build if there are Python syntax errors or undefined names\n          flake8 . --count --select=E9,F63,F7,F82 --show-source --statistics\n          # exit-zero treats all errors as warnings. The GitHub editor is 127 chars wide\n          flake8 . --count --exit-zero --max-complexity=10 --max-line-length=127 --statistics\n\n  testing:\n    needs: linting\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        python-version: [\"3.11\", \"3.14-dev\"]\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up Python ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n        uses: actions/setup-python@v4\n        with:\n          python-version: ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: |\n          python -m pip install --upgrade pip\n          pip install pytest\n          if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi\n      - name: Test with pytest\n        run: |\n          pytest\n\n  security:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      actions: read\n      contents: read\n      security-events: write\n    strategy:\n      fail-fast: false\n      matrix:\n        language: [ 'python' ]\n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout repository\n        uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Initialize CodeQL\n        uses: github/codeql-action/init@v2\n        with:\n          languages: ${{ matrix.language }}\n      - name: Autobuild\n        uses: github/codeql-action/autobuild@v2\n      - name: Perform CodeQL Analysis\n        uses: github/codeql-action/analyze@v2\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771169117781}}
{"type":"message","id":"d5f1fcb4","parentId":"8989ce75","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:25:27.539Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing File Contents**\n\nI've got the initial file content in front of me now. Currently, I'm poring over the README.md file, specifically the CI badge section, trying to parse its meaning and implications for the project's overall structure and development pipeline.\n\n\n**Investigating File Changes**\n\nI'm now examining the `README.md` and `ci-cd.yml` files closely. I've noted the current and target CI badge URLs in the README and plan to swap them. I'm also pivoting to the `ci-cd.yml` file, where I intend to replace the unstable Python version `3.14-dev` with `3.13`. I'm going to integrate a dry run environment variable to prevent network calls during testing.\n\n\n**Assessing Actionable Items**\n\nI've distilled the requirements into a concrete action plan, ready for implementation. The primary focus now is the README.md and ci-cd.yml files. My immediate task involves swapping the CI badge URLs in README.md and modifying the Python version in the CI/CD workflow from `3.14-dev` to `3.13`. Furthermore, I've outlined the addition of a `DRY_RUN` environment variable to facilitate local testing and prevent unnecessary network calls, using `pytest` to verify the changes.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771169127422_409","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"[![CI](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/ci-cd.yml?branch=dev)](https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/actions/workflows/ci-cd.yml)","oldText":"[![CI](https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/actions/workflows/ci-cd.yml/badge.svg?branch=dev)](https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/actions/workflows/ci-cd.yml)","file_path":"README.md"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771169127531_410","name":"edit","arguments":{"oldText":"    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        python-version: [\"3.11\", \"3.14-dev\"]","newText":"    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        python-version: [\"3.11\", \"3.13\"]\n    env:\n      DRY_RUN: true","file_path":".github/workflows/ci-cd.yml"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":6713,"output":723,"cacheRead":5140,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":7436,"cost":{"input":0.013425999999999999,"output":0.008676,"cacheRead":0.001028,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.023129999999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771169117782}}
